annotationA: Translationally controlled tumor protein (Tctp) belongs to the TCTP family. It interacts with the GTPase Rheb to regulate organ growth. Tctp is required for DNA damage response and genome stability
annotationB: 60S ribosomal protein L18a; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization; Belongs to the eukaryotic ribosomal protein eL20 family
